OL,3,CCould your local election be delayed
OL,4,Cbecause of Labour's devolution plans?
OL,6,FDeputy PM and local government
OL,7,Fminister Angela Rayner told a
OL,8,Fparliamentary committee on Tuesday it
OL,9,Fwould be "ludicrous" for councils to
OL,10,Fhave elections if they're changing
OL,11,Ftheir structures.
OL,13,FRayner initially said the delay
OL,14,F"wouldn't be for longer than a couple
OL,15,Fof months" but could be up to "a year".
