OL,3,CCould your local election be delayed
OL,4,Cbecause of Labour's devolution plans?
OL,6,FSome councils have come forward but
OL,7,Faren't happy about having to delay the
OL,8,Felections - like Norfolk, where
OL,9,Fcouncil leader Kay Mason Billig said
OL,10,Fthe government was pushing councils to
OL,11,Ftake a decision with "indecent haste"
OL,12,Fand to apply to postpone elections.
OL,14,FBut the council decided the
OL,15,Falternative was to be at the back of
OL,16,Fthe queue for powers and funding,
OL,17,Fwhich they didn't want.
