OL,3,CCould your local election be delayed
OL,4,Cbecause of Labour's devolution plans?
OL,6,FThe District Councils Network said:
OL,7,F"This is likely to mean that the local
OL,8,Felectorate has no ability to cast its
OL,9,Fverdict on plans ` which were not
OL,10,Fmentioned in Labour's general election
OL,11,Fmanifesto ` to replace highly
OL,12,Flocalised district councils with mega
OL,13,Fcouncils with populations in excess of
OL,14,Fhalf a million people.
OL,16,F"We are concerned that reorganisation
OL,17,Fis being rushed, with councils given
OL,18,Funtil 10 January to decide if they
OL,19,Fsought to delay elections in response
OL,20,Fto the English Devolution White Paper,
OL,21,Fpublished on 16 December."
